 null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I suggest to implement method .cloned for Iterator<Item = &mut T>. Currently this method only works for iterators with Item = &T.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nlet mut source = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\", \"d\"].map(String::from);\r\nlet mut iter = source.iter_mut();\r\nlet sp: Vec<String> = iter.by_ref().take(2).map(|x| x.clone()).collect(); // works correctly\r\nlet fp: Vec<String> = iter.by_ref().take(2).cloned().collect(); // error[E0271]\r\n```\r\n\r\nError message:\r\n```\r\nerror[E0271]: type mismatch resolving `<std::iter::Take<&mut std::slice::IterMut<'_, String>> as Iterator>::Item == &_`\r\nnote:\r\n    expected reference `&_`\r\n    found mutable reference `&mut String`\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.58.1 (db9d1b20b 2022-01-20)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: db9d1b20bba1968c1ec1fc49616d4742c1725b4b\r\ncommit-date: 2022-01-20\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.58.1\r\nLLVM version: 13.0.0\r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/93199/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/93199/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}